.TH "s2io_change_mtu" 9 "s2io_change_mtu" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
s2io_change_mtu \- entry point to change MTU size for the device.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" s2io_change_mtu
.BI "(struct net_device *dev "  ","
.BI "int new_mtu "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device pointer.
.IP "new_mtu" 12
the new MTU size for the device.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
A driver entry point to change MTU size for the device.
Before changing the MTU the device must be stopped.
Return value:
0 on success and an appropriate (-)ve integer as defined in errno.h
file on failure.
